  "body": "After my extensive `ERC4626` review, I would like to quickly discuss whether to add the following missing unit tests. As a reference, I refer to the existing tests at [`ERC4626.test.js`](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/test/token/ERC20/extensions/ERC4626.test.js). The coverage issue is specifically related to the `private` function `_tryGetAssetDecimals`:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n/**\r\n * @dev Attempts to fetch the asset decimals. A return value of false indicates that the attempt failed in some way.\r\n */\r\nfunction _tryGetAssetDecimals(IERC20 asset_) private view returns (bool, uint8) {\r\n    (bool success, bytes memory encodedDecimals) = address(asset_).staticcall(\r\n        abi.encodeWithSelector(IERC20Metadata.decimals.selector)\r\n    );\r\n    if (success && encodedDecimals.length >= 32) {\r\n        uint256 returnedDecimals = abi.decode(encodedDecimals, (uint256));\r\n        if (returnedDecimals <= type(uint8).max) {\r\n            return (true, uint8(returnedDecimals));\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    return (false, 0);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Add a unit test that calls a simple EOA as `asset_` at construction time (checks for `encodedDecimals.length >= 32`).\r\n- Add a unit test that calls a contract as `asset_` at construction time that returns a higher `decimals` than `type(uint8).max` (checks the condition `returnedDecimals <= type(uint8).max`). For that you can use a simple mock like that:\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.0;\r\n\r\ncontract ERC20DecimalsExcessMock {\r\n    function decimals() public pure returns (uint256) {\r\n        return type(uint256).max;\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Add a unit test that checks the overflow of `_underlyingDecimals + _decimalsOffset()`. This might be a non-issue right now, but if you add such a check and do an `unchecked` refactor at some point it should immediately throw :)\r\n\r\nLet me know what you think.",
